nary%20group%20and%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20negotiations%20resulted%20in%20Prigozhin%20calling%20off%20his%20short-lived%20mutiny%20and%20being%20cast%20into%20exile%20in%20Belarus%2C%20though%20the%20details%20were%20always%20a%20little%20unclear.%20His%20mercenaries%20were%20given%20the%20choice%20to%20join%20the%20ranks%20of%20the%20Russian%20military%2C%20leave%20for%20civilian%20life%2C%20or%20join%20Prigozhin%20in%20Belarus.%20Many%20chose%20the%20latter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Prigozhin%20has%20been%20spotted%20in%20Russia%20a%20few%20times%2C%20including%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyevgeny-prigozhin-spotted-summit-russia-wagner-group-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecritical%20Russia%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20African%20leaders%2C%20and%20seen%20in%20photos%20and%20videos%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-image-prigozhin-wagner-group-boss-maybe-at-belarus-camp-2023-7%5C%22%3Enew%20Wagner%20camp%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Belarus%2C%20where%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-mercenaries-train-belarus-troops-russia-putin-grip-power-slipping-2023-8%5C%22%3Efighters%20were%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%20Belarusian%20soldiers.%20In%20a%20video%20shared%20online%20in%20July%2C%20Prigozhin%20said%20Wagner%20forces%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprigozhin-resurfaces-in-belarus-addresses-wagner-fighters-at-camp-2023-7%5C%22%3Eremain%20in%20Belarus%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20time%20before%20heading%20to%20Africa%2C%20joining%20their%20local%20operations%20in%20several%20countries%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20those%20mercenary%20networks%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20government%20combat%20operations%20and%20training%20programs%20aimed%20at%20defeating%20rebel%20groups%2C%20as%20well%20as%20disinformation%20campaigns%20in%20the%20region.%20Wagner%20forces%20in%20Africa%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20committing%20human%20rights%20violations%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-russian-mercenaries-linked-to-killings-of-african-civilians-2022-9%5C%22%3Eatrocities%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Founder%20of%20Wagner%20private%20mercenary%20group%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6495e7a165b9ce0018a49df1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFounder%20of%20Wagner%20private%20mercenary%20group%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin.%3Cp%3EPress%20service%20of%20%26quot%3BConcord%26quot%3B%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Prigozhin's%20apparent%20death%20in%20Wednesday's%20plane%20crash%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20Wagner's%20vast%20networks%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fin-brief%2Fwhat-russias-wagner-group-doing-africa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfrica%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Latin%20America%2C%20as%20well%20who%20will%20take%20control%20of%20the%20group's%20operations%20and%20finances%2C%20remain%20the%20big%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20%26quot%3BRussia%20would%20abandon%20its%20PMC%20%5Bprivate%20military%20company%5D%20model%20altogether%20given%20that%20it%20provides%20significant%20benefits%20at%20relatively%20low%20financial%20or%20political%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Associate%20Director%20and%20Associate%20Fellow%20with%20the%20Transnational%20Threats%20Project%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20Catrina%20Doxsee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fwhat-does-death-yevgeny-prigozhin-mean-russia-and-wagner-group%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E%20shortly%20after%20Prigozhin's%20plane%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wagner%20was%20founded%20in%202014%20during%20Russia's%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20and%20began%20operating%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20state%20proxy%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Syria%2C%20and%20Libya%2C%20it%20gave%20Russia%20a%20way%20to%20increase%20its%20influence%20abroad%20while%20maintaining%20plausible%20deniability%20and%20limited%20accountability%20for%20the%20group's%20actions.%20Since%20then%2C%20its%20personnel%20and%20operations%20have%20only%20expanded%2C%20and%20Wagner%20has%20gained%20political%20capital%2C%20actual%20capital%2C%20and%20broader%20influence%20in%20certain%20areas%20and%20with%20certain%20governments%2C%20which%20favors%20Russia's%20geopolitical%20ambitions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow%20has%20looked%20at%20expanding%20its%20PMC%20network%2C%20but%20none%20have%20the%20footprint%20that%20Wagner%20does.%20And%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20a%20clear%20successor%20organization%2C%20Moscow%20is%20unlikely%20to%20dismantle%20Wagner's%20operational%20infrastructure%20in%20host%20countries%2C%20as%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20rebuild%20the%20same%20relationships%2C%20knowledge%2C%20and%20systems%20that%20Wagner%20personnel%20have%20established%20over%20the%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Doxsee%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20evidence%20that%20Wagner's%20reach%20in%20some%20countries%20such%20as%20Mali%20has%20grown%20since%20its%20June%20mutiny%2C%20suggesting%20the%20group's%20influence%20is%20not%20only%20still%20intact%2C%20but%20potentially%20growing.%20Miles%20told%20Insider%20the%20networks%20appear%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20siloed%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20that%20Prigozhin's%20absence%20wouldn't%20majorly%20impact%20their%20activities.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20key%20decisions%20still%20ran%20through%20him%20and%20his%20immediate%20group%2C%20but%20Prigozhin%20was%20not%20an%20operational%20commander.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe%20was%20good%20at%20holding%20a%20gun%20and%20screaming%20curse%20words%20into%20the%20TV%20camera%2C%20but%20not%20so%20much%20at%20actually%20leading%20men%20in%20combat.%20That%20was%20something%20that%20other%20people%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20impact%20of%20losing%20both%20Prigozhin%20and%20Utkin%20still%20majorly%20impacts%20the%20group%20in%20a%20larger%20context%2C%20namely%20their%20brand%20and%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrigozhin%20and%20Utkin%20were%20undeniably%20the%20faces%20of%20Wagner%2C%20and%20their%20assassinations%20will%20have%20dramatic%20impacts%20on%20Wagner's%20command%20structure%20and%20the%20Wagner%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20Russian%20analyst%20Kateryna%20Stepanenko.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20too%20early%20to%20tell%20how%20this%20will%20materialize%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BWagner%20commanders%20and%20fighters%20may%20begin%20to%20fear%20for%20their%20lives%20or%20become%20demoralized.%20The%20Russian%20MoD's%20%5BMinistry%20of%20Defense%5D%20and%20Kremlin's%20inroads%20into%20Wagner's%20operations%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20Prigozhin%20%E2%80%94%20who%20would%20fight%20for%20new%20opportunities%20for%20Wagner%20personnel%20%E2%80%94%20may%20further%20lead%20to%20the%20degradation%20of%20the%20Wagner%20grouping.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mural%20depicting%20Russia's%20Wagner%20Group%20that%20reads%3A%20%26quot%3BWagner%20Group%20-%20Russian%20knights.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63ee1da8dd6fcf00194aa0cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22978%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mural%20depicting%20mercenaries%20of%20Russia's%20Wagner%20Group%20that%20reads%3A%20%26quot%3BWagner%20Group%20-%20Russian%20knights.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FDarko%20Vojinovic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20time%20will%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20what%20Prigozhin's%20absence%20may%20mean%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20that%20Wagner%20will%20continue%20to%20exist%20%E2%80%94%20just%20with%20a%20rebranding%20of%20sorts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20a%20dissolution%20or%20replacement%20of%20Wagner%2C%20Russia%20is%20likely%20to%20install%20new%20Wagner%20leadership%20%E2%80%94%20with%20stronger%20loyalty%20to%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20kept%20under%20tighter%20supervision%20than%20Prigozhin%20%E2%80%94%20while%20maintaining%20as%20much%20continuity%20as%20possible%20at%20the%20operational%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20Doxsee%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20Russian-installed%20leadership%20makes%20sense%20given%20a%20lack%20of%20a%20clear%20successor%20to%20either%20Prigozhin%20or%20Utkin.%20As%20of%20this%20time%2C%20no%20Wagner%20commander%20has%20released%20a%20statement%20regarding%20Prigozhin's%20death%20or%20the%20future%20of%20the%20group%2C%20likely%20indicating%20there's%20little%20to%20speculate%20about%20a%20potential%20power%20structure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20a%20reformed%20Wagner%20will%20be%20an%20example%20of%20Russia%20tightening%20the%20leash%2C%20which%20began%20happening%20before%20Prigozhin's%20presumed%20death.%20In%20August%2C%20ISW%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment-august-14-2023%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20reports%20on%20efforts%20from%20the%20Russian%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20to%20form%20new%20private%20military%20companies%20beyond%20Wagner%20and%20recruit%20Wagner%20personnel%20for%20those%20groups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Russia%20does%20intend%20to%20keep%20a%20closer%20eye%20on%20Wagner%2C%20it%20could%20have%20consequences%2C%20Miles%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20imagine%20what%20you%20would%20see%20is%20at%20least%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20exercise%20more%20central%20government%20control%20over%20those%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20utility%20of%20Wagner%20was%20always%20plausible%20deniability%2C%20so%20if%20that%20is%20what%20they%20do%2C%20they%20erode%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-not-chicken-with-head-cut-off-without-prigozhin-expert-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692906602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e76b8a52bc2d001991292c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-not-chicken-with-head-cut-off-without-prigozhin-expert-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHe%20was%20good%20at%20holding%20a%20gun%20and%20screaming%20curse%20words%20into%20the%20TV%20camera%20but%20not%20so%20much%20at%20actually%20leading%20men%20in%20combat%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Russia%20expert%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40insider.com%20(Chris%20Panella%2CErin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwagner-not-chicken-with-head-cut-off-without-prigozhin-expert-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20military%20nominations%20delay%20could%20embolden%20adversaries%3A%20Milley%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692906152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103034833%2Cimgsize-1234994.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-military-nominations-delay-could-embolden-adversaries-milley%2Farticleshow%2F103034810.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103034810.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EGeneral%20Mark%20Milley%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%2C%20has%20warned%20that%20the%20delay%20in%20approving%20senior%20US%20military%20nominations%20due%20to%20a%20standoff%20ove