20a%20single%20case%20against%20me.%20I%20happen%20to%20be%20lawyer%20at%20a%20motor%20accident%20claims%20tribunal.%20I%20was%20a%20lawyer%20and%20I%20have%20again%20started%20practising%2C%26quot%3B%20Malhotra%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPost-conviction%2C%20whether%20licence%20to%20practise%20can%20be%20given%3F%20Law%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20noble%20profession.%20Bar%20Council%20(of%20India)%20has%20to%20say%20whether%20a%20convict%20can%20practise%20law.%20You%20are%20a%20convict%2C%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20about%20that.%20You%20are%20out%20of%20jail%20due%20to%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20you.%20Conviction%20remains%20only%20the%20sentence%20is%20cut%20short%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20sure%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Shah's%20lawyer%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%2024A%20of%20the%20Advocates%20Act%20states%20that%20a%20person%20convicted%20of%20an%20offence%20involving%20moral%20turpitude%20cannot%20be%20enrolled%20as%20an%20advocate.%20It%20also%20states%20that%20disqualification%20for%20enrolment%20shall%20cease%20to%20have%20effect%20after%20a%20period%20of%20two%20years%20has%20elapsed%20since%20his%20release%20or%20dismissal%20or%20removal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMalhotra%20submitted%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20released%20Shah%2C%20after%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20no-objection%20from%20the%20Jail%20Superintendent%2C%20Godhra%20as%20well%20as%20the%20committee%20on%20remission%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Home%20Department%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20all%20recommended%20and%20approved%20his%20premature%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20nowhere%20mentioned%20in%20either%20of%20the%20remission%20policies%20that%20all%20the%20stakeholders%20have%20to%20give%20unanimous%20opinion%20for%20release%20of%20a%20convict%20nor%20does%20it%20specify%20that%20it%20should%20be%20majority%20decision%20which%20should%20prevail%20on%20the%20decision%20making%20process.%20All%20that%20it%20says%20is%20that%20the%20State%20Government%20should%20collate%20various%20opinions%20from%20different%20quarters%20in%20order%20to%20arrive%20at%20premature%20policy%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Malhotra%20told%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20released%20the%2011%20convicts%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%201992%20remission%20policy%20and%20not%20the%20policy%20adopted%20in%202014%20which%20is%20effective%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%202014%20policy%2C%20state%20cannot%20grant%20remission%20for%20a%20crime%20investigated%20by%20the%20CBI%20or%20where%20people%20have%20been%20convicted%20of%20murder%20with%20rape%20or%20gang-rape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContending%20that%20the%20rights%20of%20victim%20are%20restricted%20under%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Sonia%20Mathur%2C%20appearing%20for%20another%20convict%20Bipin%20Chandra%20Joshi%2C%20submitted%20the%20victim%20cannot%20challenge%20judicial%20order%20on%20sentence%20pursuant%20to%20the%20trial%20as%20the%20right%20is%20confined%20to%20only%20to%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaintaining%20that%20the%20compensation%20awarded%20in%20Bilkis%20Bano's%20case%20is%20highest%20ever%20in%20a%20gang-rape%20case%2C%20Mathur%20said%20if%20there%20is%20a%20flaw%20in%20a%20process%2C%20that's%20for%20the%20State%20to%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20at%20all%20being%20insensitive%20to%20what%20has%20happened.%20No%20one%20deserves%20that.%20I%20am%20not%20submitting%20what%20has%20happened%20can%20be%20brought%20back%20by%20paying%20compensation...%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInsofar%20as%20her%20rights%20are%20concerned%2C%20she%20has%20been%20awarded%20compensation%2C%20she%20has%20been%20given%20a%20job%2C%20accommodation.%20This%20is%20what%20was%20given%20to%20her%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20(convict's)%20rights%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposing%20the%20locus%20standi%20of%20the%20PIL%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%2C%20Mathur%20said%20none%20of%20the%20parties%20here%20are%20allowed%20to%20interfere%20at%20stage%20of%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20convicts%20are%20entitled%20to%20be%20prematurely%20released%20subject%20to%20the%20condition%20being%20fulfilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMathur%20said%20even%20the%20top%20court%20has%20been%20ruling%20in%20favour%20of%20premature%20release%20of%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20wish%20you%20would%20canvass%20reformative%20theory%20for%20all%20the%20prisoners%20who%20have%20completed%2014%20years%20in%20India.%20How%20many%20remissions%20have%20taken%20place%3F%20Why%20are%20our%20jails%20overcrowded%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20remarked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMathur%20told%20the%20court%20that%20Joshi's%20wife%20is%20suffering%20from%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20case%2C%20fine%20of%20Rs%206%2C000%20has%20been%20paid%20in%202019%20and%20trial%20court%20has%20accepted%20it%20without%20objection%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%20will%20resume%20on%20August%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20on%20August%2017%20said%20state%20governments%20should%20not%20be%20selective%20in%20granting%20remission%20to%20convicts%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20reform%20and%20reintegrate%20with%20society%20should%20be%20given%20to%20every%20prisoner%2C%20as%20it%20told%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20which%20defended%20its%20decision%20of%20premature%20release%20of%20all%2011%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20an%20earlier%20hearing%2C%20TMC%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20gang-rape%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%20and%20murder%20of%20seven%20of%20her%20family%20members%20were%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrime%20against%20humanity%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20accused%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20of%20having%20failed%20to%20exercise%20its%20constitutional%20mandate%20of%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20women%20and%20children%20by%20granting%20remission%20to%20the%2011%20convicts%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bhorrendous%26quot%3B%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20petition%20filed%20by%20Bilkis%20Bano%20contesting%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20them%2C%20several%20other%20PILs%20including%20one%20by%20CPI(M)%20leader%20Subhashini%20Ali%2C%20independent%20journalist%20Revati%20Laul%20and%20former%20vice-chancellor%20of%20Lucknow%20University%20Roop%20Rekha%20Verma%20have%20challenged%20the%20remission.%20Moitra%20has%20also%20filed%20a%20PIL%20against%20the%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano%20was%2021%20years%20old%20and%20five%20months%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20gang-raped%20while%20fleeing%20the%20horror%20of%20the%20communal%20riots%20that%20broke%20out%20after%20the%20Godhra%20train-burning%20incident.%20Her%20three-year-old%20daughter%20was%20among%20the%20seven%20family%20members%20killed%20in%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692898980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-08%2Fp179al0g_bilkis-bano-ani-650_625x300_17_August_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-bilkis-bano-case-convict-how-can-you-practice-law-4326427%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20voiced%20surprise%20over%20how%20can%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gang-rape%20case%20and%20murder%20of%20her%20family%20members%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20practise%20law%20after%20his%20conviction%2C%20the%20remission%20of%20his%20sentence%20notwithstanding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-