ion%20that%20has%20been%20revealed%20publicly%20since%20they%20apparently%20exchanged%20remarks%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20Xi%20Jinping%20of%20China%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20highlighted%20India%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20on%20the%20unresolved%20issues%20along%20the%20LAC%20on%20the%20western%20sector%20of%20the%20border%20areas%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kwatra%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Johannesburg%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%9Cunderlined%20that%20the%20maintenance%20of%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20at%20borders%20and%20observing%20and%20respecting%20the%20LAC%20are%20essential%20for%20the%20normalisation%20of%20India-China%20relationship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20Indian%20diplomat%20then%20said%20that%20there%20was%20an%20understanding%20from%20both%20leaders%20for%20an%20early%20resolution%20of%20the%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20agreed%20to%20direct%20their%20relevant%20officials%20to%20intensify%20their%20efforts%20at%20expeditious%20de-escalation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20statement%20from%20China%20on%20this%20exchange%2C%20till%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20another%20question%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20Kwatra%20once%20more%20described%20the%20interaction%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconversation%E2%80%9D%2C%20indicating%20that%20New%20Delhi%20does%20not%20want%20to%20imply%20that%20it%20was%20a%20formal%2C%20structured%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20did%20not%20mention%20when%20and%20where%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconversation%E2%80%9D%20took%20place%2C%20but%20sources%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20it%20took%20place%20on%20Wednesday.%20Both%20leaders%20have%20together%20participated%20at%20various%20BRICS%20events%20for%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20last%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20took%20part%20in%20two%20sessions%20of%20the%20main%20plenary%20during%20the%20day%20and%20also%20attended%20the%20official%20dinner%20in%20the%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Thursday%2C%20both%20leaders%20were%20seen%20walking%20in%20together%20side-by-side%20at%20the%20joint%20press%20conference%2C%20with%20Modi%20apparently%20saying%20something%20to%20the%20Chinese%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%20have%20been%20in%20a%20military%20stand-off%20at%20multiple%20points%20on%20the%20LAC%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20since%20May%202020%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20death%20of%2020%20Indian%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20military%20and%20diplomatic%20talks%2C%20there%20has%20been%20withdrawal%20of%20troops%20at%20around%20four%20friction%20points%20which%20has%20led%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20buffer%20zones%20where%20no%20country%20is%20allowed%20to%20patrol.%20It%20essentially%20meant%20that%20the%20Indian%20army%20cannot%20patrol%20at%20around%2026%20patrolling%20points%20that%20they%20had%20access%20to%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20still%20two%20strategic%20points%20%E2%80%93%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok%20%E2%80%93%20where%20India%20and%20China%20have%20been%20unable%20to%20reach%20any%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20last%20Friday%2C%20senior%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20military%20commanders%20have%20engaged%20in%20a%20series%20of%20back-to-back%20discussions%20at%20the%20Major%20General%20level%20that%20were%20seen%20as%20a%20scene-setter%20for%20a%20much-anticipated%20bilateral%20meeting%20between%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20at%20BRICS%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foreign%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20mention%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20was%20a%20change%20from%20the%20situation%20last%20time%20when%20the%20two%20leaders%20had%20talked%20with%20each%20other%20at%20the%20dinner%20for%20G-20%20summit%20in%20Bali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20photo%20surfacing%20of%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20standing%20and%20talking%20with%20each%20other%2C%20Kwatra%20had%20then%20only%20mentioned%20that%20there%20was%20an%20exchange%20of%20pleasantries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20China%20had%20not%20mentioned%20the%20encounter%20then%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20minister%20Wang%20Yi%20referred%20to%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20consensus%20stabilising%20China-India%20relations%20in%20Bali%E2%80%9D%20at%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwang-yi-ajit-doval-india-china-brics%5C%22%3Emeeting%20with%20Indian%20national%20security%20advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20that%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Feight-months-later-india-says-modi-xi-did-talk-about-stabilising-ties-at-bali-encounter%5C%22%3EMEA%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20leader%20had%20%E2%80%9Cexchanged%20courtesies%20and%20also%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20to%20stabilise%20our%20bilateral%20relations%E2%80%9D%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692898174000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F10123822%2FModi-with-Xi-Jinping.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20was%20their%20first%20direct%20conversation%20that%20has%20been%20revealed%20publicly%20since%20they%20apparently%20exchanged%20remarks%20in%20November%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%2