ads%20to%20now%20doing%20a%20lead%20show%20the%20actor%20shares%20his%20interesting%20journey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SHRUTI%20SAMPAT%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Fexclusive-tellyblazer-dhruv-taras-ishaan-dhawan-recalls-having-no-money-2-years-back-i-couldnt-even-think-about-booking-tickets-back-home-paise-khatam-ho-gaye-the%2Farticleshow%2F103029957.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Day%2010%20of%20Article%20370%20Hearing%3A%20Union%20Govt%20Says%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Accession%20Was%20Not%20Unique%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Solicitor%20General%20(SG)%20Tushar%20Mehta%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2024%2C%20told%20the%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20hearing%20the%20challenges%20to%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20not%20the%20only%20princely%20state%20with%20its%20own%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%2062%20princely%20states%20had%20their%20own%20constitutions%20in%201939.%20He%20added%20that%20many%20princely%20states%20did%20not%20sign%20instruments%20of%20merger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20wanted%20to%20be%20apprised%20of%20how%20many%20out%20of%20the%20562%20states%20did%20not%20execute%20merger%20agreements.%20He%20wanted%20to%20be%20convinced%20whether%20the%20execution%20of%20merger%20agreement%20was%20not%20quintessential%20to%20the%20acceptance%20of%20final%20sovereignty%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20CJI%20and%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20found%20the%20SG%E2%80%99s%20submission%20on%20the%20question%20of%20sovereignty%20insufficient.%20They%20asked%20him%20to%20answer%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20claim%20that%20despite%20its%20integration%20with%20India%20and%20surrender%20of%20external%20sovereignty%2C%20the%20internal%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20state%20remained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20didn%E2%80%99t%20find%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20argument%20of%20equating%20the%20state%20Constituent%20Assembly%20with%20the%20state%20legislative%20assembly%20persuasive.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20bench%20is%20avoiding%20a%20dialogue%20at%20this%20stage%20with%20him%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20because%20it%20wanted%20him%20to%20complete%20the%20list%20of%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutlining%20the%20history%20of%20the%20accession%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Mehta%20claimed%20that%20the%20moment%20the%20accession%20is%20complete%2C%20the%20sovereignty%20gets%20lost%20as%20it%20gets%20subsumed%20with%20the%20larger%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20claimed%20that%20after%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20residents%20now%20enjoy%20a%20large%20number%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20other%20rights%20that%20they%20were%20previously%20not%20entitled%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mehta%2C%20the%20significance%20of%20reading%20down%20Article%20370%20lies%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20ended%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpsychological%20duality%E2%80%9D%20which%20existed%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20people.%20He%20also%20claimed%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20an%20obstacle%20preventing%20them%20from%20enjoying%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20welfare%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Attorney%20General%20(AG)%20R.%20Venkataramani%20had%20submitted%20to%20the%20bench%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20enjoyed%20plenary%20power%20during%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20and%20that%20it%20followed%20due%20process%20while%20passing%20the%20Presidential%20Orders%20revoking%20the%20erstwhile%20state%E2%80%99s%20special%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AG%20also%20sought%20to%20impress%20upon%20the%20bench%20that%20it%20ought%20to%20defer%20to%20the%20wisdom%20of%20Parliament%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20reorganisation%20of%20border%20states%20like%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20AG%2C%20Article%20370%20was%20designed%20to%20aid%20the%20constitutional%20integration%20process%20on%20the%20same%20line%20as%20it%20happened%20with%20other%20states.%20He%20added%20that%20its%20continuance%20over%20a%20period%20could%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20distortion%20of%20its%20original%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20AG%20claimed%20that%20Article%20370%E2%80%99s%20objective%20was%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20integration%20with%20the%20Union%2C%20the%20CJI%20argued%2C%20suggesting%20that%20ends%20cannot%20justify%20the%20means%20and%20that%20means%20should%20be%20consistent%20with%20the%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AG%2C%20without%20elaborating%2C%20quoted%20Abraham%20Lincoln%20on%20balancing%20and%20losing%20the%20nation%2C%20and%20preserving%20the%20constitution.%20He%20answered%20that%20a%20limb%20can%20be%20amputated%20to%20save%20a%20life%2C%20but%20a%20life%20is%20never%20sacrificed%20to%20save%20a%20limb.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692886200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fday-10-of-article-370-hearing-union-govt-says-jks-accession-was-not-unique%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20J%24K%20was%20not%20the%20only%20princely%20state%20with%20its%20own%20constitution.%20He%20sought%20to%20rebut%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20arguments%20that%20linked%20the%20state's%20special%20status%20with%20its%20Instrument%20of%20Accession.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%