rew%20316.8%20lakh%20tonnes%20of%20onion%20in%202021-22.%20Onion%20production%20in%202022-23%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20310%20lakh%20tonnes.%20Maharashtra%20continues%20to%20be%20the%20dominant%20producer%20of%20onions%2C%20accounting%20for%2040.7%25%20of%20domestic%20production%20(126.4%20lakh%20tonnes)%20while%2016.6%25%20comes%20from%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(51.5%20lakh%20tonnes).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFactors%20affecting%20sensitivity%20of%20onions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnion%20is%20a%20climate%20sensitive%20crop%20as%20winter%20frost%2C%20high%20summer%20temperatures%20and%20untimely%20rainfall%20can%20hamper%20its%20yield.%20Untimely%20rains%20in%20April%20damaged%20the%20crop.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagricoop.nic.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FMonthly%2520Report%2520on%2520Onion%2520for%2520May%252C%25202018.pdf%5C%22%3EOnions%20are%20consumed%20round%20the%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%2060-65%25%20production%20is%20in%20Rabi%20(sown%20in%20November-December%20and%20harvested%20in%20April).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKharif%20onion%20is%20sown%20in%20June-July%20and%20is%20harvested%20in%20October-November.%20The%20late%20Kharif%20crop%20is%20sown%20in%20September-October%20and%20is%20harvested%20in%20December-January.%20Kharif%20and%20later%20Kharif%20produce%20about%2020%20percent%20each.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERabi%20onions%20are%20stored%20for%20consumption%20between%20June-September.%20The%20farmers%20have%20also%20created%20storage%20structures%20under%20various%20schemes%20of%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015-16%2C%20Modi%20government%20set%20up%20a%20Price%20Stabilisation%20Fund%20(PSF)%20that%20could%20be%20used%20to%20procure%20agricultural%20produce%20at%20market%20prices.%20In%20the%20first%20year%20itself%2C%20Small%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Agri-Business%20Consortium%20and%20National%20Agricultural%20Cooperative%20Marketing%20Federation%20of%20India%20Ltd.%20(NAFED)%20procured%20onions%20which%20were%20later%20sold%20in%20Delhi%20and%20other%20places%20through%20Mother%20Dairy.%20PSF%20has%20since%20been%20used%20to%20create%20buffer%20stock%20of%20onion%20and%20pulses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20for%202023-24%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2Feb%2Fvol1.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Union%20budget%20provides%20only%20a%20token%20amount%20of%20Rs%201%20lakh%20for%20PSF%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPrice%20outlook%20for%202023-24%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20fluctuation%20in%20price%20realisation%20by%20farmers.%20Figure%201%20shows%20wholesale%20prices%20of%20onion%20of%20Lasalgaon%2C%20Maharashtra%20and%20Azadpur%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMandi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Delhi.%20The%20wholesale%20prices%20of%20onion%20stood%20at%20only%20Rs%2013.25%20per%20kilogram%20(kg)%20in%20July%202023%20in%20Lasalgaon%20and%20it%20was%20Rs%2014.4%20per%20kg%20in%20Azadpur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20retail%20price%20of%20onion%20in%20New%20Delhi%20was%20Rs%2032.3%20per%20kg%20in%20July%202023%2C%20up%20from%20Rs%2026%20per%20kg%20in%20June%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20price%20rise%20seems%20to%20have%20persuaded%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Fgovernment-procures-3-lakh-tonnes-of-onion-for-buffer-stock-526191%5C%22%3Erelease%20stock%20from%20onions%3C%2Fa%3E%20procured%20under%20PSF.%20On%20August%2011%2C%20the%20government%20announced%20sale%20of%20onion%20from%20its%20buffer%20stock.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFigure%201%3A%20Wholesale%20and%20retail%20prices%20of%20onions%20at%20Lasalgaon%20(the%20largest%20wholesale%20onion%20market)%20and%20Delhi%3C%2Fb%3E%3C