Fspan%3E%20August%2023%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20former%20diplomat%20said%20that%20he%20discovered%20%E2%80%9Chow%20communal%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20prime%20minister%20was%20during%20a%20discussion%20on%20secularism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20on%20my%20Ram%20Rahim%20Yatra%20from%20Rameshwaram%20to%20Ayodhya%2C%20I%20was%20summoned%20from%20Odisha%20to%20come%20back%20to%20Delhi%20and%20Narasimha%20Rao%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20don%E2%80%99t%20disagree%20with%20your%20yatra%20but%20I%20do%20have%20a%20disagreement%20with%20your%20definition%20of%20secularism.%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20315px)%2085vw%2C%20315px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res.jpeg%20796w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res-199x300.jpeg%20199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res-679x1024.jpeg%20679w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22474%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3A%20The%20First%20Fifty%20Years%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EJuggernaut%20(August%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20I%20asked%20him%2C%20%E2%80%98Sir%2C%20what%20is%20wrong%20with%20my%20definition%20of%20secularism%3F%E2%80%99%20and%20his%20reply%20which%20has%20remained%20engraved%20in%20my%20heart%20and%20on%20my%20soul%20was%2C%20%E2%80%98Mani%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20that%20this%20is%20a%20Hindu%20country%E2%80%99.%20I%20sat%20up%20in%20my%20chair%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98This%20is%20what%20the%20BJP%20says.%20(But)%20this%20is%20not%20a%20Hindu%20country.%20We%20are%20a%20secular%20country%20and%20in%20this%20secular%20country%20we%20have%20a%20huge%20majority%20of%20Hindus%20but%20we%20also%20have%20nearly%20200%20million%20Muslims%20and%20several%20other%20Christians%2C%20Jews%2C%20Parsis%20and%20Sikhs.%20So%20how%20can%20we%20be%20a%20Hindu%20country%3F%20We%20can%20only%20be%20a%20secular%20country.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20because%20Narasimha%E2%80%99s%20mind%20was%20so%20partisan%2C%20was%20so%20sectarian%20that%20he%20led%20this%20country%20from%20the%20secular%20path%20to%20the%20communal%20path.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERao%20served%20as%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpv-narasimha-rao-new-india-legacy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprime%20minister%20from%201991%20to%201996%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20While%20his%20term%20is%20usually%20associated%20with%20the%20initiation%20of%20economic%20liberalisation%20reforms%20in%201991%2C%20his%20tenure%20also%20saw%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20In%20the%20ensuing%20communal%20riots%2C%20thousands%20lost%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAiyar%E2%80%99s%20book%20traces%20his%20journey%20as%20a%20diplomat%20in%20the%20Indian%20Foreign%20Service%20with%20a%20significant%20stint%20in%20Pakistan%20(as%20consul%20general%20in%20Karachi%20from%20December%201978%20to%20January%201982)%3B%20and%20his%20relationship%20with%20former%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20also%20traces%20his%20observations%20during%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20in%201984%20%E2%80%93%20following%20the%20assassination%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%20%E2%80%93%20and%20questions%20government%20decisions%20taken%20during%20that%20time%20to%20control%20the%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20companion%20volume%20will%20examine%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi-era%20in%20detail%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20published%20soon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Wanted%20to%20vote%20against%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20following%201984%20Sikh%20Riots%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20about%20choosing%20to%20write%20in%20detail%20about%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20Aiyar%20said%20that%20while%20he%20wanted%20to%20vote%20against%20him%20following%20the%201984%20riots%2C%20working%20with%20him%20showed%20what%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwonderful%20character%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%2C%20which%20has%20been%20hidden%20from%20the%20public%20eye.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%2082%20years%20old%2C%20the%20doctors%20tell%20me%20another%20two%20decades%20to%20go%20but%20I%20am%20not%20quite%20sure%20that%20they%20are%20right.%20So%20I%20put%20down%20my%20memories.%20And%20this%20book%20has%20about%20200%20pages%20in%20which%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20name%20is%20not%20mentioned.%20He%20only%20came%20into%20my%20life%20when%20as%20prime%20minister%20he%20incorporated%20me%20in%20his%20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20been%20very%20skeptical%20and%20I%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20voting%20booth%20to%20vote%20against%20him%20because%20of%20the%20Sikh%20pogrom.%20But%20fortunately%20or%20unfortunately%2C%20my%20name%20was%20not%20on%20the%20voting%20rolls%20so%20I%20could%20not%20vote%20against%20him.%20But%20despite%20that%2C%20he%20summoned%20me%20to%20his%20office%20and%20then%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20I%20saw%20what%20a%20wonderful%20man%20he%20was.%20And%20that%20wonderful%20character%20of%20the%20man%20has%20been%20hidden%20from%20public%20eyes%20by%20the%20media%20particularly%20%E2%80%93%20and%20also%20by%20all%20these%20traitors%20who%20cheated%20him%20and%20went%20away.%20And%20it%20is%20they%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Left%2C%20the%20liberals%20%E2%80%93%20who%20brought%20the%20BJP%20back.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBecause%20the%20BJP%20at%20that%20time%20had%20two%20seats.%20Because%20of%20V.P.%20Singh%2C%20they%20got%2088%20seats.%20And%20now%20for%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20we%20have%20been%20suffering%20this%20awful%20majoritarian%2C%20authoritarian%20rule.%20I%20only%20pray%E2%80%A6%20but%20alas%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20pray%2C%20because%20I%20am%20an%20atheist.%20But%20I%20pray%20to%20the%20forces%20that%20this%20awful%20era%20of%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20is%20brought%20to%20an%20end%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other%20in%202024.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbad-advice-rajiv-gandhi-mistakes-babri-masjid%5C%22%3EHow%20Bad%20Advice%20Led%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20To%20Make%20Mistakes%20in%20Handling%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20Issue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Pakistan%20will%20remain%20an%20albatross%20around%20our%20neck%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20engage%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20while%20speaking%20to%20senior%20journalist%20Vir%20Sanghvi%20during%20the%20launch%2C%20Aiyar%20recalled%20his%20experiences%20in%20Karachi%20while%20he%20was%20posted%20there.%20He%20said%20that%20dialogue%20with%20Pakistan%20is%20crucial%20to%20ending%20the%20demonisation%20of%20Indian%20Muslims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIs%20Pakistan%20an%20enemy%20country%3F%20My%20answer%20to%20that%20is%3A%20Pakistanis%20are%20not%20enemies.%20The%20government%20of%20Pakistan%20does%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20which%20make%20it%20an%20enemy%20of%20ours.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20they%20are%20reacting%20or%20provoking%20us.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20we%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20do%20surgical%20strikes%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20guts%20to%20sit%20across%20a%20table%20and%20talk%20to%20them.%20Why%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20talk%20to%20them%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAiyar%20said%20that%20Pakistan%20is%20ceasing%20to%20be%20a%20foreign%20policy%20issue%20in%20present%20day%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPakistan%20is%20ceasing%20to%20be%20a%20foreign%20policy%20issue%20and%20is%20becoming%20a%20domestic%20issue.%20Because%20the%20word%20Pakistan%20and%20Pakistani%20are%20being%20used%20as%20dog%20whistles%20to%20indicate%20the%20Indian%20Muslim%20community.%20Salman%20Khan%2C%20Aamir%20Khan%2C%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20%E2%80%93%20all%20have%20been%20told%20to%20go%20to%20Pakistan.%20Why%20not%20Bangladesh%20or%20Indonesia%3F%20So%20that%20the%20prejudices%20that%20we%20have%20against%20Pakistanis%20are%20transferred%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20icons%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20needs%20to%20%E2%80%9Cengage%20with%20Pakistan%20like%20Manmohan%20Singh%20and%20arrive%20at%20a%20four-point%20draft%20agreement%20that%20was%20not%20on%20visa%20or%20films%20or%20Bollywood%20songs%20or%20trade%20it%20was%20on%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20should%20deploy%20the%20talents%20of%20our%20foreign%20services%20by%20engaging%20with%20Pakistan.%20If%20not%2C%20we%20are%20wasting%20their%20talents.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20long%20as%20we%20are%20not%20able%20to%20engage%2C%20Pakistan%20will%20remain%20an%20albatross%20around%20our%20neck.%20How%20will%20we%20advise%20Russia%20when%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20Pakistan%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140721%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi-2.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140721%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi-2.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140721%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi-2-300x176.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140721%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi-2-1024x599.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140721%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi-2-425x250.jpeg%20425w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669582%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%20and%20Vir%20Sanghvi%20speak%20at%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20book%20%E2%80%98Memoris%20of%20a%20Maverick%E2%80%99.%20Photo%3A%20Sravasti%20Dasgupta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Admired%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20only%20after%20working%20with%20him%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20book%20delves%20into%20some%20detail%20about%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20years%2C%20Aiyar%20said%20that%20his%20admiration%20for%20the%20former%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20his%20junior%20at%20Doon%20School%20in%20Dehradun%20%E2%80%93%20only%20came%20after%20he%20started%20working%20with%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHere%20is%20a%20man%20who%20was%20a%20pilot%20till%20the%20other%20day.%20How%20will%20he%20become%20a%20prime%20minister%3F%E2%80%9D%20Aiyar%20recalled%20himself%20thinking.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20only%20after%20I%20saw%20how%20he%20ran%20this%20country%2C%20I%20came%20to%20admire%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20his%20forthcoming%20companion%20volume%20would%20deal%20with%20the%20controversies%20that%20surrounded%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministership%2C%20including%20the%20Bofors%20deal%20and%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20case.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20problem%20was%20that%20I%20was%20no%20confidant%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20he%20thought%20that%20I%20was%20politically%20naive.%20He%20never%20consulted%20me%20and%20never%20took%20my%20advice%20on%20anything%20political%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReferring%20to%20an%20audience%20question%20on%20an%20excerpt%20from%20his%20book%20that%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbad-advice-rajiv-gandhi-mistakes-babri-masjid%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epublished%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethat%20refers%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20advice%E2%80%9D%20that%20was%20given%20to%20Gandhi%20in%20the%20handling%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20issue%2C%20Aiyar%20said%20that%20it%20only%20shows%20that%20he%20is%20%E2%80%9Ceven-handed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20biggest%20mistake%20that%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20made%20was%20bringing%20this%20awful%20R.K.%20Dhawan%20to%20the%20PMO%2C%20which%20was%20immediately%20politicised%2C%20which%20was%20otherwise%20an%20office%20of%20technical%20advice%20without%20looking%20into%20politics%20but%20without%20compromising%20the%20principles%20of%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20entering%20active%20political%20life%20in%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%2C%20Aiyar%20went%20on%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20Union%20minister%20for%20panchayati%20raj%2C%20petroleum%20and%20natural%20gas%20and%20youth%20affairs%20and%20sports%20in%20subsequent%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202017%2C%20he%20was%20briefly%20suspended%20from%20the%20Congress%20party%20over%20his%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-suspends-mani-shankar-aiyar-neech-remark-pm-modi%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Cneech%E2%80%9D%20remark%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eagainst%20Modi%2C%20which%20mushroomed%20into%20a%20massive%20controversy%20just%20ahead%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20polls.%20In%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202014%20general%20election%2C%20he%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fmodi-can-never-become-pm-can-sell-tea-mani-shankar-aiyar%2F%5C%22%3Ekicked%20up%20a%20storm%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20mocking%20Narendra%20Modi%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctea-seller%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAiyar%E2%80%99s%20book%20launch%20saw%20a%20packed%20audience%2C%20among%20whom%20was%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20and%20a%20host%20of%20former%20diplomats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692869439000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24140741%2FMani-Shankar-Aiyar-Vir-Sanghvi.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpv-narasimha-rao-mani-shankar-aiyar-book-launch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20former%20diplomat%20turning%20Congress%20politician%20also%20said%20that%20Pakistan%20is%20%E2%80%98ceasing%20to%20be%20a%20foreign%20policy%20issue%20and%20becoming%20a%20domestic%20issue'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A47%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpv-narasimha-rao-mani-shankar-aiyar-book-launch%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20strengthen%20grouping%2C%20says%20PM%20Modi%20as%20Brics%20adds%206%20countries%20to%20group%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692869149000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsm