e-mumbai-domestic-help-stand-up-comedian%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estand-up%20comic%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20podcaster%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20was%2014%20when%20he%20knew%20he%20was%20queer%20(gay).%20But%20he%20was%20also%20raised%20as%20a%20staunch%20Catholic.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20tried%20to%20first%20do%20away%20with%20that%20%5Bfeeling%20attracted%20to%20boys%5D%20by%20joining%20Bible%20camps.%20When%20I%20was%20in%20Class%208%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20priests%20coming%20to%20our%20church%20recognised%20me%20as%20a%20very%20talented%20and%20outspoken%20child.%20At%20a%20very%20young%20age%2C%20I%20was%20groomed%20to%20become%20a%20Catholic%20priest.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20realised%20I%20like%20men%20and%20that%20duality%20set%20in.%20So%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20it%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20until%20I%20was%2019%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Navin%2C%20speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavin%20first%20came%20out%20to%20his%20best%20friend%20Amit%2C%20who%20he%20knew%20since%20they%20were%2010.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20already%20knew%20each%20other%20very%20well%2C%20although%20we%20were%20never%20friends%20who%20spoke%20about%20personal%20stuff.%20So%2C%20when%20I%20came%20out%20to%20him%2C%20it%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20fact.%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20came%20out%20to%20him%20and%20nothing%20changed%20after%20that%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20being%20gay%20is%20really.%20People%20who%20know%20you%2C%20know%20you%20for%20who%20you%20are.%20What%20gender%20you%20sleep%20with%20barely%20makes%20a%20difference%20to%20them%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20he%20was%2021%20and%20in%20his%20third%20year%20of%20college%2C%20he%20had%20come%20out%20to%20most%20of%20his%20friends.%20He%20says%20he%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20tell%20all%20his%20friends%20and%20acquaintances%20that%20he%20was%20gay%20because%20he%20had%20begun%20feeling%20left%20out%20from%20their%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20also%20wanted%20to%20chime%20in%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20people%20would%20share%20weird%20notions%20of%20what%20gay%20people%20are%20with%20me.%20Listening%20to%20them%2C%20I%20found%20some%20of%20their%20notions%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F152754%2Fiit-madras-kaushik-section-377-supreme-court%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egay%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20hilarious.%20They%20had%20no%20idea%20about%20gay%20people%20and%20how%20we%20exist.%20That%20became%20the%20subject%20of%20my%20first%20comedy%20set%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Queer%20Comedian%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028.jpg%201365w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028-500x500.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028-768x768.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FNavin-Noronha-01-1691803028-96x96.jpg%2096w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-327138%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENavin%20Noronha%20is%20giving%20a%20platform%20to%20other%20queer%20comedians.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EQueer%20comics%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Navin%20was%2023%2C%20he%20started%20doing%20stand-up%20comedy%20seriously.%20During%20these%20open%20mics%2C%20he%E2%80%99d%20take%20all%20these%20notions%20that%20his%20friends%20had%20of%20gay%20people%2C%20and%20turn%20them%20into%20jokes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20came%20out%20to%20his%20friend%2012%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%20began%20performing%20as%20a%20full-time%20comic%20eight%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20has%20changed.%20After%20years%20of%20touring%2C%20he%20released%20his%20first%20special%20%E2%80%98The%20Good%20Child%E2%80%99%20on%20YouTube%20in%20late%20June%202023.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20Navin%20has%20not%20only%20spread%20laughter%2C%20but%20also%20curated%20a%20lineup%20of%20LGBTQ%2B%20performers.%20They%20went%20on%20tour%20to%20Delhi%20in%20June%20and%20Mumbai%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20were%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20us%20comics%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Ayushi%20Jagad%2C%20Manvendra%20Singh%2C%20Ankur%20Tangde%20and%20I%20%E2%80%94%20who%20were%20openly%20talking%20about%20our%20queer%20lives.%20Today%2C%20we%20have%20about%2020%20comics%20who%20are%20out%20and%20proud.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20done%20sold%20out%20shows%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Mumbai%2C%20and%20are%20looking%20to%20do%20the%20same%20in%20Bengaluru%20and%20Kolkata%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Navin.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20that%20it%20takes%20grit%2C%20money%2C%20and%20resources%20to%20set%20up%20these%20shows.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20queer%20comics%2C%20we%20want%20to%20create%20spaces%20where%20other%20queer%20people%20can%20just%20vibe%2C%20thrive%20and%20nobody%20can%20tell%20us%20anything.%20I%20live%20for%20that.%20What%20we%20have%20done%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20is%20try%20our%20best%20to%20make%20t